2.10	Battle_of_Komarow	Battle of Komarów	The Battle of Komarów was one of the most important battles of the Polish-Bolshevik War. It took place on August 31, 1920, near the village of Komarowo (now Komarów) near Zamość. It was the biggest cavalry battle in the history of war since 1813 and the last great battle of any significance in which cavalry was used as such and not as mounted infantry.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Komarow.png/220px-Komarow.png
